reviews.review_text:
First Night at Shoreline Thanx Russ.  A decent recording of an average show.  Jerry's guitar is a bit low in the mix.  I am grateful to have it as it has probably never made my collection and have been seeking it for decades.  I went to this show hoping for a little more from the venue.  Lots  of people, steep slope on the lawn, and spotty sound, though it could be great in the right spot.  I still remember the landfill smell that was prominent during the early shows.  I came to enjoy shows there as long as I was down low.  I had tickets for the first ever shows at Shoreline the year prior but Jerry took a long nap and another band got the honors.
This show generally lacks conviction.  1st set highlights are Far From Me and Let It Grow.  The Grow starts to get out there before the last chorus, but is brief.
There is almost no jamming in the second set.  China/Rider and Gimme are fun as usual especially with Phil singing early on the Gimme.  Give it a listen first.  Peace
